 notion d’inclusion, un portrait global des initiatives actuelles en inclusion scolaire francophone au Canada, ainsi que des réflexions portant sur les relations entre le Moi et l’Autre, aussi bien au plan des identités ethnoculturelles que des orientations sexuelles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aEDUCATION / Inclusive Education.2bisacsh1 aBenimmas, Aïcha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorri-Anadon, Corina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlson Berg, Laurie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlson Berg, Laurie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDalley, Phyllis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacquet, Marianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRousseau, Nadia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuest-Paquette, Anne-Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSt-Vincent, Lise-Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978276372398340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782763723983423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782763723983/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles